# Testing Standards

## Framework

- Use **Vitest** (or Jest) with TypeScript support.
- Co-locate test files next to source: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`.

## Naming

- `describe` blocks match the class/function name.
- `it` blocks use the pattern: `it("should <expected behavior> when <condition>")`.

## Structure

Follow **Arrange → Act → Assert** in every test.

```typescript
it("should throw InvalidIdError when id is empty", () => {
  // Arrange
  const emptyId = "" as TaskId;

  // Act
  const act = () => getTask(emptyId);

  // Assert
  expect(act).toThrow(InvalidIdError);
});
```

## Coverage

- Unit-test all domain entities, value objects, and use cases.
- Integration-test repository implementations against a real or in-memory DB.
- Mock only infrastructure boundaries (DB, HTTP, file system) — never mock domain logic.

## Principles

- Tests must be deterministic — no reliance on wall-clock time or network.
- Prefer dependency injection over module mocking.
- One assertion per logical concept; multiple `expect` calls are fine if they verify the same behavior.
